main event: A white, bright light object was observed near New Paltz, New York on November 9, 1963.
interesting points: The object traveled at a high speed of approximately 1,400 mph.
The object passed through the sky and disappeared in the east.
The sighting was observed through ground radar and lasted for 5 minutes.
The high speed and disappearance of the object indicate it was likely an astronomical object or possibly an aircraft.
The brief duration of the sighting made it difficult to draw any firm conclusions.
